close_reason: "Implemented evidence-weighted next-action ranking, addressed review feedback, and verified release gate plus real pm CLI smoke test."
body: "Agents need an intuitive way to choose the next actionable pm item without reading every item body. Enhance pm-brief next with evidence-weighted explanations and confidence so project management stays context management while reducing token waste.\n\nImplemented evidence-weighted next-action ranking on 2026-06-12. Ranking now emits score, confidence, and compact evidence reasons covering priority, unblockability, active dependencies, fanout, stale age, linked docs/files, release, and deadline proximity. Added --explain and --confidence to pm brief next text output; JSON output includes structured ranking metadata. Verification: npm run release:check passed, and real CLI smoke test passed with pm install . --project followed by pm brief next --count 5 --explain --confidence --format json against this repo's pm data.\n\nReview feedback addressed on 2026-06-12: ranking now treats only active/open dependency targets as blockers, uses all open workspace items for dependency/fanout scoring even when filters are applied, reuses precomputed RankEvidence when materializing BriefItem output, and adds regression coverage for work blocked only by closed items. Verification after the fix: npm run release:check passed with 17 tests and real pm CLI smoke test passed with pm install . --project plus pm brief next --count 5 --explain --confidence --format json.\n\nSecond review feedback addressed on 2026-06-12: deadline scoring now avoids the negative-zero boundary and gives overdue items a stronger boost than due-today items; scoreBreakdown reuses precomputed RankEvidence. Added deadline urgency regression coverage. Verification: npm run release:check passed with 18 tests, audit:prod 0 vulnerabilities, pack dry-run, and changelog check.\n\nReview cleanup: aligned explainNextItems score breakdown with all rank components and reused a shared active item id set in buildBrief to avoid redundant ranking context work.\n\nGemini follow-up addressed: requiredContext now deduplicates dependency/link entries before prompt rendering and token estimation, with regression coverage to keep duplicate docs/files from inflating agent handoff prompts.\n\nGemini follow-up addressed: duplicate relationship IDs now collapse before dependency/dependent counts, BriefItem dependency lists, required context, and score breakdowns; added regression coverage for repeated deps entries.\n\nGemini follow-up addressed: simplified uniqueStrings with Set semantics, passed precomputed activeIds through selectNextItems/explainNextItems into BriefItem materialization, and escaped titles in plain text next-work output so multi-line titles cannot break the format."
